list.abstract: 「这小子将会改变流行音乐的风貌。」葛莱美奖潮流音乐製作人Pharrell Williams（*Britney Spears、Jay-Z、Snoop Dogg）
《CONTRAST》是日本创作男歌手秦基博的首张录音室专辑，该专辑共收录12首歌曲，于2007年9月26日由AUGUSTA RECORDS发行。 该专辑发行后凭借2.5万的销量获得日本公信榜专辑周榜5位，由此成为秦基博首张进入该榜前五位的专辑作品。

yingyinNormal.en: What did you do? Did you change the contrast or brightness settings on the television? No.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你对他干了啥？你改了电视机的对比度和亮度？没啊。

yingyinNormal.en: We thought the contrast between the femininity of the florals and the more raw, rough-hewn background would create this wonderful tension between...
yingyinNormal.zh: 通过印花图案的柔弱，与硬朗、粗糙环境的对比可以促使一种特殊的张力在…

yingyinNormal.en: Two wolves, actually. When we pumped up the contrast in the video, we saw a shadow on the wall from someone behind the camera.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是两人的行动，实际上，我们调高了视频的对比度后在墙上发现有一个从摄像机后投影出的人影。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: compare in such a way as to emphasize differences

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>contrast</highlight>, suppose you give a reasonable argument: that full-time workers should not have to live in poverty.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，假设你给出了一个合理的论点：全职工人不应该生活在贫困中。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>contrast</highlight>, only five of the 30 children paired with the "unreliable" tester participated in a follow-up activity.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，与“不可靠”测试者配对的30名儿童中，只有5名参加了后续活动。

examination_example.sentence: Immersive reading, by <highlight>contrast</highlight>, depends on being willing to risk inefficiency, goallessness, even time-wasting.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，沉浸式阅读依赖于愿意冒效率低下、无目的甚至浪费时间的风险。

sense_info_list.en: compare in such a way as to emphasize differences

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>contrast</highlight>, our own lives are governed by numbers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，我们自己的生活是由数字支配的。

examination_example.sentence: Lancy <highlight>contrasts</highlight> this with what happens in America.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 朗姿将此与美国的情况进行了对比。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>contrast</highlight>, being alone can actually be a blessing, particularly when you've actively chosen it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，独处实际上是一种福气，尤其是当你主动选择独处的时候。

examination_example.sentence: Balance television viewing with other <highlight>contrasting</highlight> activities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 平衡看电视和其他差异活动。

examination_example.sentence: The researchers advise that adults over the age of 50 should try and ensure that television viewing is balanced with other <highlight>contrasting</highlight> activities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究人员建议50岁以上的成年人应该努力确保看电视与其他差异活动的平衡。

examination_example.sentence: In <highlight>contrast</highlight>, California, home of Silicon Valley, recently proposed far more restrictive rules that would require human drivers be ready to take the wheel, and commercial use of self-driving technology.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，硅谷所在州加利福尼亚州最近提出了限制性更强的规则，要求驾驶员做好驾驶准备，并在商业上使用自动驾驶技术。
